<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 1:54PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Showers will impact portions of southeastern Tuscola, Sanilac,
Lapeer, northeastern Wayne, eastern Oakland, Macomb, St.
Clair and southeastern Huron Counties through 330 PM EDT...
At 153 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers along a line
extending from near Mayville to near Oxford to near Dearborn.
Movement was northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
Showers producing pea sized hail will be near...
Mayville around 200 PM EDT.
Kingston around 205 PM EDT.
Almont and Dryden around 210 PM EDT.
Downtown Detroit around 215 PM EDT.
Imlay City and Detroit Zoo around 220 PM EDT.
Warren and Capac around 230 PM EDT.
Grosse Pointe around 235 PM EDT.
Argyle and Emmett around 240 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>Expect a brief interval of small hail.</instruction>
